OL,6,F"I loved the idea of making a
OL,7,Fdifference and you have a window of
OL,8,Fopportunity to do so while you are a
OL,9,Fcustodian. With great privilege comes
OL,10,Fgreat responsibility.
OL,12,F"It is going to be a massive wrench to
OL,13,Fleave. I am terribly upset and feel
OL,14,Fvery emotionally attached to the
OL,15,Fbuilding but it is time now to hand
OL,16,Fover the keys."
OL,18,FPeter Bass is the manager at Appleby
OL,19,FCastle and explains part of the
OL,20,Fhistory of the building and how it is
OL,21,Fused in modern times.
